Gov. Babagana Zulum of Borno has relieved the state Head of Service (HOS), Mr Mohammed Hassan, of his appointment. Alhaji Usman Shuwa, the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), made the disclosure in a statement on Tuesday in Maiduiguri. Shuwa disclosed that the governor also approved the appointment of Mr Simon Malgwi, as the new HOS, adding that the appointment was with immediate effect. “Gov. Babagana Zulum has relieved Mohammed Hassan of his appointment as the HOS with immediate effect. “He has accordingly approved the appointment of Barrister Simon Malgwi, as the new HOS,” he said. Shuwa added that until his appointment, Malgwi was the Solicitor General and Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Education. Vanguard Nigeria News By Ndahi Marama, Maiduguri Borno state governor, prof. Bababgana Umara Zulum has directed the Secretary to the State Government, Alh. Usman Jidda Shuwa and the Head of Service, Hassan Bulama to immediately transfer all the staff of the Pension Board and salaries from top to bottom as result of anomalies… October 24, 2019 In "News" Governor Kashim Shettima of Borno state has approved with immediate effect the appointment of a new Head of Service (HoS) in person of Architect Yerima Sale. August 19, 2017 In "News" For a successful rehabilitation and reconstruction process of the present administration, Borno State Governor, Babagana Zulum, yesterday, directed the Secretary to the State Government, SSG, Usman Shuwa, to immediately order the Shehus of Dikwa and that of Bama Local Government Areas to immediately relocate to their respective palaces. August 1, 2019 In "News"